Dependencies:
-------------
- SDL
- SDL_image
- SDL_ttf
- SDL_net
- X11 (including MesaGL and MesaGLU)
- OpenAL
- FreeALUT
- libvorbis
- LibXml2 (optional)
- Lua

On Linux you have to install packages that provide those libraries.
For Windows build, all dependencies are included.

Controls:
---------
mouse or arrow keys - look
WASD                - move
Shift               - run
Space               - jump
Ctrl                - crouch (toggle)
Alt                 - freelon (3rd person only) (toggle)
p                   - step over small obstacles, e.g. walk up the stairs (toggle)
m                   - 1st/3rd person camera (toggle)
i                   - reincarnate/disappear

right click         - use
middle click        - grab/drop when holding an object or take from inventory
wheel up            - throw (when holding an object)
wheel down          - put into inventory
tab                 - interface mode (toggle)

f                   - point gesture
g                   - fall back gesture
h                   - salute gesture
j                   - wave gesture
k                   - flip out gesture
l                   - all animations

F11                 - screenshot (saved to ~/.openzone/screenshot-DATE.bmp)
F12                 - minimize and freeze

Notes:
------

- On first run ~/.openzone/client.rc (or ~/.openzone/client.xml) configuration file
  with default settings is generated. Edit it to change the settings.
- On exit the world is saved to ~/.openzone/default.ozState. Delete this file to start with a
  clean world again.
- You can jump to higher places with jump-duck (like in Half-Life 1).
- "~" means $HOME on Linux (i.e. /home/username) and $USERPROFILE on Windows (i.e.
  C:\Documents and Settings\username on Windows XP or C:\Users\username on Windows Vista)

Settings:
---------

Format:
- XML, example:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<config>
  <var name="variable1_name" value="variable1_value"/>
  <var name="variable2_name" value="variable2_value"/>
  ...
  <var name="variableN_name" value="variableN_value"/>
</config>

- or .rc, example:

variable1_name    "variable1_value"
variable2_name    "variable2_value"
...
variableN_name    "variableN_value"



Types:

bool   - "true" or "false"
int    - integer (as decimal integer value in C)
float  - floating point value (as in C)
string - arbitrary string



Variables:
name    [type]    default value

dir.data [string] "data"
  path to static game data directory (textures, sounds, maps, models)

home.dir [string] "~/.openzone" for Linux, "" for Windows ("" = current directory = data directory)
  path to home directory where configuration files, saved states, screenshots and logs reside

input.keys.xSens [float] 0.2
  sensitivity for left/right arrow keys

input.keys.ySens [float] 0.2
  sensitivity for up/down arrow keys

input.mouse.xSens [float] 0.2
  sensitivity for x mouse axis

input.mouse.ySens [float] 0.2
  sensitivity for y mouse axis

net.port [int] 6666
  server port (network not supported yet)

net.server [string] "localhost"
  server hostname (network not supported yet)

render.camera.smoothCoef [float] 0.3
  camera smoothing coefficient

render.camera.thirdPerson [bool] false
  whether camera should be in 3rd person mode on startup

render.camera.thirdPersonDistance [float] 2.5
  distance of camera behind model's head when in 3rd person

render.dayVisibility [float] 300.0
  day visibility range in meters

render.drawAABBs [bool] false
  if AABBs around objects should be drawn

render.nightVisibility [float] 100.0
  night visibility range in meters

render.particleRadius [float] 0.5
  particle radius (currently not used)

render.perspective.angle [float] 80.0
  vertical camera angle, horizontal angle is adjusted based on aspect ratio

render.perspective.aspect [float] 0.0
  aspect ratio (H/V), if 0.0 it's automatically calculated from resolution

render.perspective.max [float] 400.0
  initial perspective matrix max distance (unimportant as later overwritten by xxxVisibility)

render.perspective.min [float] 0.1
  minimum distance for perspective matrix

render.showAim [bool] false
  whether a small green box should be projected to the point the player is aiming

render.waterDayVisibility [float] 8.0
  day visibility under water in meters

render.waterNightVisibility [float] 4.0
  night visibility under water in meters

screen.bpp [int] 32
  screen mode bits per pixel

screen.full [bool] false
  fullscreen mode

screen.height [int] 768
  screen mode vertical resolution

screen.leaveScreensaver [bool] true
  don't disable screensaver (sometimes it remains disabled after exit, it's a SDL bug; if we don't
  disable it, it's just OK, since it won't ever start in fullscreen mode)

screen.nvVSync [bool] true
  set __GL_SYNC_TO_VBLANK=1 environment variable. On X11 it enables VSync on NVidia cards,
  otherwise it does no harm.

screen.width [int] 1024
  screen mode horizontal resolution

sound.volume.effects [float] 1.0
  sound effects volume (0.0 - mute, 1.0 - max volume)

sound.volume.music [float] 1.0
  music volume (0.0 - mute, 1.0 - max volume) (currently there's no music loaded)

tick [int] 20
  Milliseconds between two world updates. Should be 20 to match real time.

ui.cursor.arrow [string] "cursors/left_ptr.png"
ui.cursor.arrow.hotspot.x [int] 1
ui.cursor.arrow.hotspot.y [int] 1
ui.cursor.arrow.size [int] 32
  arrow cursor

ui.cursor.move [string] "cursors/fleur.png"
ui.cursor.move.hotspot.x [int] 16
ui.cursor.move.hotspot.y [int] 16
ui.cursor.move.size [int] 32
  move cursor

ui.cursor.hand [string] "cursors/hand2.png"
ui.cursor.hand.hotspot.x [int] 16
ui.cursor.hand.hotspot.y [int] 16
ui.cursor.hand.size [int] 32
  hand cursor (not used yet)

ui.cursor.text [string] "cursors/xterm.png"
ui.cursor.text.hotspot.x [int] 16
ui.cursor.text.hotspot.y [int] 16
ui.cursor.text.size [int] 32
  text cursor (not used yet)

ui.cursor.x [string] "cursors/X_cursor.png"
ui.cursor.x.hotspot.x [int] 16
ui.cursor.x.hotspot.y [int] 16
ui.cursor.x.size [int] 32
  X cursor (not used yet)

ui.font.mono.file [string] "fonts/DejaVuSansMono.ttf"
ui.font.mono.height [int] 12
  fixed-width font file and height (must be TrueType)

ui.font.sans.file [string] "fonts/DejaVuSans.ttf"
ui.font.sans.height [int] 11
  normal font file and height (must be TrueType)

ui.font.title.file [string] "fonts/DejaVuSans.ttf"
ui.font.title.height [int] 14
  title font file and height (must be TrueType)
